==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Separable
<hw>Sep"a*ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>separabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>s⟦eacute⟧parable</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being separated, disjoined, disunited, or divided;
<as>as, the <ex>separable</ex> parts of plants; qualities not
<ex>separable</ex> from the substance in which they exist.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sep"a*ra*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Sep"a*ra*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trials permit me not to doubt of the <qex>separableness</qex> of a
yellow tincture from gold.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separate</ent>⟦br⟧
